solution.p:
Since the fractions don't have the same denominator, we have to make them have like denominators.  You should multiply the first fraction by \frac{2}{2}.

                            \frac{}{a} + \frac{}{2a}    \amp = \frac{2 \cdot}{2a} + \frac{}{2a} 
                                                                                        \amp =  \frac{2 \cdot +}{2a}
                                                                                        \amp =

