solution.p:
f(x) = x^{2}+bx+c  \amp = \left(x + \frac{b}{2}\right)^{2} - \frac{b^{2}}{4} +c 
                       \amp = \left(x + \frac{b}{2}\right)^{2} - \frac{b^{2}}{4} +\frac{4c}{4} 
                       \amp = \left(x + \frac{b}{2}\right)^{2} + \frac{4c-b^{2}}{4}

Thus, the vertex is (\frac{-b}{2},\frac{4c-b^{2}}{4}).
